        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Based on low-angular resolution NH2D maps (30arcsec) obtained with IRAM 30-m, which shows emission in the region around the filament, 
we know that the line should be ~1K, while some of the isolated hyperfine structure components it is ~0.5K. 
Therefore, we need to achieve an rms of 0.1K to clearly detect the satellite components and 
obtain well constrained line profiles to then fit. 

Requested sensitivity: The expected  NH2D (11,1-10,1) brightness (in the faint regions) is 0.1 K in a 0.1 k/ms channel and 6arcsec beam. 
The 6arcsec beam is requested to match our previous NH3 observations.

Imaging requirements: 3 pointing mosaic is needed to cover the region of interest (the filament), but we don't need ACA because the emission is compact (&lt;15arcsec).
Correlator setup: 3 spws with 117MHz bandwidth and spec. avg. of 2, or a 0.07kms spectral resolution, and 1 spw for continuum with 1.8GHz bandwidth. 
The other 2 spectral line basebands will be used to observe other deuterated molecules.</prj:justificationText>
