    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose ALMA Cycle 2 observations that will provide the first study of the fragmentation 
of an isothermal filament within the Barnard 5 dense core where the turbulence is subsonic. 
The fragmentation will be probed by searching for places with higher levels of deuteration and/or higher column densities 
using high density tracers: N2H+(3-2), N2D+(3-2), and NH2D (1_(1,1)-1_(0,1)). 
This is the first time that such an analysis can be carried out to understand the substructure within dense cores, 
and will have implications for how important substructures are in the star formation process. 
This can only be done now because of the sensitivity provided by ALMA, but also because our selected target is 
nearby we can finally reach the angular resolutions needed to study this crucial process.
</prp:abstract>
